# About

To repeatedly execute logic, one can use loops. One of the most common loop types in C# is the `while` loop, which keeps on looping until a Boolean condition evaluates to `false`.

```csharp
int x = 23;

while (x > 10)
{
    // Execute logic if x > 10
    x = x - 1;
}
```

